Color
: Pink but lateral part of carapace and P2–4 pale, abdomen translucent (

Poupin & Corbari 2016: fig. 9f; 
Fig. 23
D, reproduced here by permission of Laure Corbari

).

Distribution . Bahamas (Cay Sal Bank), Puerto Rico , Guadeloupe , off St. Vincent , Barbados , and Brazil ( Pernambuco );
161– 453 m
. Benedict (1901) recorded this species based on two lots taken by the U.S. F.C. Fish Hawk from Puerto Rico . One of these from Station 6070 was examined (see under Material). The other lot from Station 6065 could not be located. The latter material was recorded from an unusually shallow depth between 4–6 fms, which depth record remains questionable.
